	<div class="commentBody">	
		<div id="comment_body_6822807">If you have a look on <a href="http://www.armadilloaerospace.com/" title="armadilloaerospace.com">his page</a> [armadilloaerospace.com], you'll find the answers. His engines work by reacting hyrogen peroxide over platinum-plated meshes. These meshes are pretty expensive, and most of the engines have many layers of them to achieve full catylsation. Also remember that (IIRC) they have either four or five engines, as the engines are used for attitude control.<br> <br>And platinum ain't cheap.</div>
	</div>

